Description: Complete seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a flat area with plant impressions from a basket (?), on all sides around this string impressions of a twisted cord with a width of 0.2 cm. The top shows an oval scarab-like seal-impression with a standing figure on a line on the right, facing to the left with a falcon head (?). The arms are hanging down on each side of the body with the right arm transitioning into the tail of an upright cobra, facing to the left. Above another unrecognisable sing.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
